 samples. Where can I get them?'),(303,88,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(304,88,'english-content','The LaCTAD provides some basic protocols for the preparation of some specific types of analysis, but it is advisable to follow the instructions of the manufacturer of the reagents you will be using.'),(305,88,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(306,88,'section',''),(307,88,'_section','field_552c330c4622f'),(308,89,'_edit_last','1'),(309,89,'field_55525b8b4a9d2','a:11:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_55525b8b4a9d2\";s:5:\"label\";s:5:\"Image\";s:4:\"name\";s:5:\"image\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"save_format\";s:6:\"object\";s:12:\"preview_size\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:7:\"library\";s:3:\"all\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(311,89,'position','normal'),(312,89,'layout','no_box'),(313,89,'hide_on_screen',''),(314,89,'_edit_lock','1431460724:1'),(315,89,'rule','a:5:{s:5:\"param\";s:9:\"post_type\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:10:\"equipments\";s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;s:8:\"group_no\";i:0;}'),(316,90,'_wp_attached_file','2015/04/3730xl_small.jpg'),(317,90,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:650;s:6:\"height\";i:600;s:4:\"file\";s:24:\"2015/04/3730xl_small.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(318,53,'image','90'),(319,53,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(322,52,'image','92'),(323,52,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(324,92,'_wp_attached_file','2015/04/44-16836HiSeq.jpg'),(325,92,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:2519;s:6:\"height\";i:1875;s:4:\"file\";s:25:\"2015/04/44-16836HiSeq.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(326,93,'_edit_last','1'),(327,93,'_edit_lock','1431543153:1'),(328,93,'english-title','Confocal Microscopy'),(329,93,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(330,93,'english-content','The Confocal Microscopy is a key tool for most studies in Cell Biology, in all of biological areas, as it allows the visualization of cells or tissues enabling the location of proteins within cells and the visualization of the interaction between proteins. Confocal microscopy can be a complementary  technique to Flow Cytometry enabling the location of cells, organelles or other subcell components which express the particularities on the surface or cytoplasmic proteins in tissue sections, using digital image in high resolution.\r\n\r\nThe samples can be seen by labeling for immunofluorescence with different fluorochromes. The techniques should be appropriate to the type of sample and procedure.\r\n\r\nThe Confocal microscopy is useful for make images in 2D (two dimensional) e 3D (three dimensions).\r\n\r\nIn Confocal microscope all structures out of focus are eliminated of the image, leaving the image with better definition and depth of field compared to conventional optical microscopy. Another advantage over conventional optical microscopy is the capacity that the Confocal microscopy have to do images in optical sections for thicker samples, enabling the subsequent overlapping of images to form a 3D image.\r\n\r\nConfocal microscopy can be used for:\r\n\r\n- Observation of cells and tissues labeled with fluorochromes by immunofluorescence.\r\n\r\n- Construction of 3D images\r\n\r\n- Colocalization\r\n\r\n- Observation of the physiological state of cells and tissues\r\n\r\nOther techniques can be implemented on Confocal Microscopy.\r\n\r\nLinks of free software of analysis result of Confocal Microscopy:\r\n\r\n- LAS Lite download: <a href=\"ftp://ftp.llt.de/softlib/LAS_AF_Lite/\">ftp://ftp.llt.de/softlib/LAS_AF_Lite/</a>\r\n\r\n- ImageJ download: <a href=\"http://rsbweb.nih.gov/ij/\">http://rsbweb.nih.gov/ij/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(331,93,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(332,95,'_edit_last','1'),(333,95,'_edit_lock','1431543233:1'),(334,95,'english-title','Multiplex Immunoassay'),(335,95,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(336,95,'english-content','The Multiplex immunoassay performs dosages of hormones and cytokines. This technique is widely used in experiments on human physiology and health sciences. Being able to perform a wide variety of bioassays in a quick, accurate and cost-effective way. This technology is based on the simultaneous analysis of multiple proteins and the quantification of more than 100 different analytes with small sample volumes (10 to 50 uL).\r\n\r\nThe principal materials used in the Multiplex Immunoassay are serum, plasma and cell culture supernatant. However, besides these, it can use adipose tissue interstitial fluid, cerebral fluid, synovial fluid, urine, cell lysate, tissue of the central nervous system, spleen, colon, lung, liver, and others.\r\n\r\nA Multiplex Immunoassay may be useful in the following applications:\r\n\r\n- Cytokine Assay\r\n- Analysis of protein expression\r\n\r\nOther techniques of Multiplex Immunoassay can be implemented.\r\n\r\nThis technology can replace a conventional ELISA or ELISPOT or Western blot, with many advantages over them, such as time savings, because it makes several measurements (up to 100) in the same well, using small amounts of sample (10 to 50 uL), and high specificity, sensitivity and reproducibility.\r\n\r\nSamples must be delivered to LaCTAD properly identified and stored in dry ice to maintain quality of the service.\r\n\r\nThe parameters will be selected as desired.\r\n\r\nThe manipulation is done on LaCTAD. Which includes to put the sample in the plate, the washing steps, calibration of the apparatus, the reading of samples and results.\r\n\r\nThe laboratory can buy the kits and assay necessary to perform the experiments, or request them to LaCTAD.\r\n\r\nThe LaCTAD works with the following kit suppliers:\r\n\r\nMillipore:<a href=\"http://www.millipore.com/\"> http://www.millipore.com/</a>\r\nBio-rad: <a href=\"http://www.biorad.com/\">http://www.biorad.com/</a>\r\nLife Technologies: <a href=\"http://www.invitrogen.com/site/us/en/home.html\">http://www.invitrogen.com/site/us/en/home.html</a>\r\n\r\nIf the user wants to use kits from other suppliers should contact the LaCTAD to suitability analysis for the equipment.'),(337,95,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(338,96,'_edit_last','1'),(339,96,'_edit_lock','1431543312:1'),(340,96,'english-title','Mass Spectrometry'),(341,96,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(342,96,'english-content','The mass spectrometry service is an important tool for qualitative and quantitative applications, in a form that allows confidently quantifying and confirming trace components in a complex samples with ease, speed and accuracy.\r\n\r\nThis is a technique which consists of determining molecular weights (ESI-MS) of compounds, identifies, quantifies and determines post-translational modifications of proteins and compounds using LC-MS/MS, and achieves a more comprehensive and reliable result, even with lower quantities traces of complex samples.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(343,96,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(344,97,'_edit_last','1'),(345,97,'_edit_lock','1431543459:1'),(346,97,'english-title','Isothermal Titration Calorimetry'),(347,97,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(348,97,'english-content','Isothermal Titration Calorimetry is a technique which measures, in calorimetric terms, biomolecular interactions in liquid samples including protein-small molecule, protein-protein, protein-enzyme, inhibitor-enzyme, protein-DNA, among others.\r\n\r\nWhen substances bind with each other in a biomolecular event, heat is generated or absorbed. In this way, this technique directly measures the thermodynamic heat released in the case of exothermic reactions, or absorbed in case of endothermic reactions. The measurement of this heat allows precise and simultaneous determination of binding parameters as binding constants (K), stoichiometry of the reaction (n), enthalpy (∆H), entropy (∆S) and variation of the heat capacity. This provides a complete thermodynamic profile of molecular in a single experiment. The ITC technique goes beyond binding affinities and can elucidate the mechanism of molecular interaction, and has become the method of choice for characterization of biomolecular interactions.\r\n\r\nThere is a wide area where the ITC technique can be applied, among which is the molecular interactions characterization of small molecules, proteins, antibodies, nucleic acids, lipids, others biomolecules, and evaluation of changes in the molecular structure of binding mechanisms and biological activity.\r\n\r\nThe advantages of this method are highlighted by determinations at the nanomolar and picomolar level without molecular weight limitations or Buffers restrictions. In addition, it can easily accommodate colored or turbid solutions, or particles in suspension and automated operations provide simultaneous determination of thermodynamic parameters which can not be obtained by another methods.'),(349,97,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(350,98,'_edit_last','1'),(351,98,'_edit_lock','1431545046:1'),(352,99,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/SP5_II_system_prod_b_cl_13_0a7b14c5eb.jpg'),(353,99,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:500;s:6:\"height\";i:350;s:4:\"file\";s:49:\"2015/05/SP5_II_system_prod_b_cl_13_0a7b14c5eb.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(354,98,'english-title','Leica TCS SP5 II Microscope'),(355,98,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(356,98,'english-content','The LaCTAD in the area of Cell Biology is equipped with a Confocal Microscope from Leica, Model TCS SP5 II, that produces fluorescent images of a variety of materials of biological samples such as cells and tissues. The Leica TCS SP5 II provides high resolution images by fluorescence microscopy, both for cells fixed and stained with fluorescent probes and for living cells with functional indicators  and/or molecules conjugate with GFP and derivatives.\r\n\r\nThe equipment consists of lasers Argon, Helium and Helium-Neônio543 Neônio633 and the objective 10x, 20x and 63x, the latter being available only in the immersion oil.\r\n\r\nWith this equipment it is possible to perform high-resolution optical sections for forming 3D images.\r\n\r\nIn Confocal microscope all structures out of focus are suppressed in the image formation.\r\n\r\nIn this equipment techniques such as optical sections are also available'),(357,98,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(358,98,'image','106'),(359,98,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(360,100,'_edit_last','1'),(361,100,'_edit_lock','1431544536:1'),(362,101,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/lsr_bioplex_sub_200reader.jpg'),(363,101,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:470;s:6:\"height\";i:302;s:4:\"file\";s:37:\"2015/05/lsr_bioplex_sub_200reader.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(364,100,'english-title','Multiplex Immunoassay Bio-plex 200'),(365,100,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(366,100,'english-content','The LaCTAD of Cell Biology area is equipped with Multiplex Immunoassay  of Bio-Rad brand, Bio-plex  200 model, capable of measurements of cytokines and hormones, quickly and accurately. The machine has two internal lasers for reading different samples with the following wavelengths 532nm (green) and 635nm (red) combined with a digital signal processor “real-time” that distinguishes more than 100 different analytes.\r\n\r\nEach user is responsible for the preparation, storage and forwarding their samples to our service.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(367,100,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(368,100,'image','101'),(369,100,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(370,102,'_edit_last','1'),(371,102,'_edit_lock','1431544645:1'),(372,103,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/407609__Cx83tp3yJ7frdSuYaluB6Dor.jpg'),(373,103,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:700;s:6:\"height\";i:525;s:4:\"file\";s:44:\"2015/05/407609__Cx83tp3yJ7frdSuYaluB6Dor.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(374,102,'english-title','Flow Cytometer FACS Canto II'),(375,102,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(376,102,'english-content','The Cell Biology LaCTAD has a FACS Canto II (BD Biosciences), capable to perform 8 parameters analysis (six colors, size and complexity) of a large number of cells – or any other kind of particle size between 0.2 and 50μm – in a short period of time.\r\n\r\nThe equipment has a blue laser (488 nm) and red (635 nm), and filters 530/30 nm (FITC), 585/42 nm (PE), 660/20 nm (APC), 695/40 nm (PerCP-Cy5.5), and 2 filters 780/60 nm: PE-Cy7 (excited by 488nm laser), and APC-Cy7 (excited by 635nm laser).\r\n\r\nThe BD FACS Diva™ software is used for the acquisition and data analysis. Our service also includes the FCAP Array, which performs the analysis of CBA – Cytometric Bead Array.\r\nIn future, our service will provide computers with other softwares for data analysis.'),(377,102,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(378,102,'image','103'),(379,102,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(380,104,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/TCS_SP5_1_c20524b2d3.jpg'),(381,104,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:500;s:6:\"height\";i:330;s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"2015/05/TCS_SP5_1_c20524b2d3.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(382,105,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/TCS-SP5IIfa.jpg'),(383,105,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:500;s:6:\"height\";i:330;s:4:\"file\";s:23:\"2015/05/TCS-SP5IIfa.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(384,106,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/TCS-SP8.jpg'),(385,106,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:629;s:6:\"height\";i:615;s:4:\"file\";s:19:\"2015/05/TCS-SP8.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(386,107,'_edit_last','1'),(387,107,'_edit_lock','1431545488:1'),(388,108,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/xevo_tqs_hi_res.jpg'),(389,108,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:1410;s:6:\"height\";i:1409;s:4:\"file\";s:27:\"2015/05/xevo_tqs_hi_res.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:14;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:10:\"NIKON D300\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1222855876;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:2:\"34\";s:3:\"iso\";s:3:\"200\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:3:\"1.6\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(390,107,'english-title','Mass Spectrometry Xevo Q-TOF MS'),(391,107,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(392,107,'english-content','The LaCTAD Proteomics is equipped with a Xevo Q-TOF MS Waters.\r\n\r\nThis mass spectrometer (partnership with the Central Institute of Analytical Chemistry) is a LC-MS/MS type instrument, composed of a Waters UPLC nanoACQUITY liquid chromatography coupled to a Waters Xevo mass spectrometer with a platform quadrupole-time of flight (Q-TOF) and equipped with a nanoeletrospray source (nanoESI). It accesses the highest levels of content information from more challenging samples so that they can reliably confirm and quantify trace components in more complex samples with ease, speed, and precision. It has excellent sensitivity and selectivity to offer high quality, accurate mass measurements and reproducible measurements of routine data.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Designed with ACQUITY UPLC ® technology which leverages the benefits of speed and chromatography with higher resolution and sensitivity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Method electrospray ionization (nanoESI).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>mass analyzer Q-TOF.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processor and mass analyzer Mascot.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(393,107,'_english-content','field_5501d641a0ad1'),(394,107,'image','108'),(395,107,'_image','field_55525b8b4a9d2'),(396,110,'_edit_last','1'),(397,110,'_edit_lock','1431545589:1'),(398,111,'_wp_attached_file','2015/05/USMM-86WC5K-1331039668713.jpg'),(399,111,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:500;s:6:\"height\";i:751;s:4:\"file\";s:37:\"2015/05/USMM-86WC5K-1331039668713.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:14:\"STURE EKENDAHL\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(400,110,'english-title','Liquid chromatography AKTA Purifier'),(401,110,'_english-title','field_5501d1e0ba3d9'),(402,110,'english-content','The LaCTAD Proteomics is equipped with an FPLC AKTA Purifier Model GE, a liquid chromatography device designed for analysis and purification of proteins. This comprises: a system of pumps which control (s) the rate (s) flow (s) (s) of buffer (s) for a liquid chromatography column which has a wide range of packaging / resin varying as possible chromatographic techniques be used, such as ion exchange, gel filtration, hydrophobic interaction and affinity; by a detector of UV absorption at 280 nm combined with a monitor UPC-900, which provides measurements of pH, conductivity and concentration gradient archiving data for each analysis and an automated fraction collector, Frac-920.\r\n\r\nAllows a maximum flow rate of 20 mL / min and a maximum pressure of 5 MPa and able to operate scale mg.\r\n\r\nThe software used in this equipment is UNICORN version 3.2.\r\n\r\nSome of the columns are recommended for use in FPLC-AKTA Purifier:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lactad.unicamp.br/?page_id=1021&amp;lang=en\">Request services</a>\r\n<table border=\"0\" frame=\"VOID\" rules=\"NONE\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"LEFT\" bgcolor=\"#999999\" width=\"229\" height=\"16\"><strong>Coluna de Troca Iônica</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"LEFT\" bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" height=\"16\"><strong>Código / Nome da coluna</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"LEFT\" height=\"16\">17-1153-01 / HiTrap™ Q, 1 ml</td>